      "step_content": "All birds can fly. Penguins are birds. Penguins cannot fly. Therefore penguins are birds.",
      "summary": "The model contradicts itself inside one step. Rules can't catch that — this is where the expensive tiers earn their keep.",
      "aftermath": "In production: the judge catches the contradiction, T2.5 rewrites the step ('All birds are descended from theropod dinosaurs. Penguins are birds. Penguins cannot fly.'), and the corrected step replaces the broken one in the response.",
      "beats": [
