        {
          "target_tier": "t1",
          "dwell_ms": 4000,
          "copy": "T1 runs because it's cheap. Twenty milliseconds of rules. But we don't have a 'detect-faulty-logic' rule — writing one would mean enumerating every kind of broken argument a human can make. That's the LLM's job, and it would cost too much to run for free on every step."
