          "target_tier": "t2",
          "dwell_ms": 4400,
          "copy": "Now the LLM judge runs because the cheap tier couldn't resolve it. Sixty milliseconds. It reads the step and the prompt and asks: 'does this reasoning hold together?' This is where the LLM beats the regex — it understands that 'all X fly' and 'this X doesn't fly' can't both be true."
        },
        {
          "target_tier": "t2_5",
          "dwell_ms": 4000,
          "copy": "Then T2.5 — the model itself — gets a turn. About a hundred milliseconds. It either says 'OK' if it stands by its step, or writes a one-line 'Correction:' with a rewritten version. This is where the broken syllogism would get rewritten."
        },
